COPYWRITING EXCELLENCE FRAMEWORK
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

HEADLINE BEST PRACTICES:
✓ Lead with benefit, not feature
✓ Create curiosity or promise transformation
✓ Use power words: "discover", "unlock", "finally", "proven" (only if substantiated)
✓ Make it scannable - assume 2-second attention span
✗ Don't waste characters on brand name (it's shown separately)
✗ Avoid generic phrases: "check this out", "click here"

PRIMARY TEXT BEST PRACTICES:
✓ Hook (first 20 chars): Stop the scroll with relatable pain point or desire
✓ Bridge: Present solution with specific benefit from Authorized Claims
✓ Close: Clear call-to-action with value reinforcement
✓ Use "you" language - make it personal
✓ Create micro-commitments: "See how...", "Discover why..."
✗ Don't bury the lede - get to value fast
✗ Avoid jargon unless audience expects it

DESCRIPTION BEST PRACTICES:
✓ Reinforce core benefit or add urgency (if compliant)
✓ Can be a secondary benefit from Authorized Claims
✗ Don't repeat the headline verbatim

PERSUASION TECHNIQUES (Use 2-3):
- Social proof: "Thousands choose..." (only if substantiated)
- Specificity: Use exact numbers from Technical Specifications
- Contrast: Before/after states (emotional, not unproven physical claims)
- Scarcity: Time-limited offers (only if in Authorized Claims)
- Authority: Certifications, testing, credentials (only if in Authorized Claims)

